Students will observe and analyze the work of a speech therapist with a CLP  and voice disorder client. Students will learn to exercise their voice and will aquire an overview of objective voice assessment methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To apply the theoretical knowledge about voice disorder prevention, voice therapy and speech disorders in velopharyngeal dysfunction in practical speech therapy sessions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student can assess symptoms of speech impairment associated with clefting and symptoms of voice disorder.  The student can explain the mechanism of voice and CLP speech. The student can choose the intervention/treatment methods and specific materials to be used in therapy sessions using the help of speech therapist or lecturer.  The student is able to plan a therapy session with child with cleft palate impairment.
